#Combine other similar features
fifa['Ball_Skills']=(fifa.Dribbling*fifa['Skill Moves']*fifa.BallControl)/3
fifa['Phys_Skills']=(fifa.Positioning*fifa.Stamina*fifa.Strength*fifa.Agility)/4
fifa['Quickness']=(fifa.SprintSpeed*fifa.Acceleration*fifa.Agility)/3
fifa['Total_Passing']=(fifa.ShortPassing*fifa.LongPassing)/2

        'Quickness_boxcox', 'Age_Middle', 'Age_Old']]

Using the same variables, the KNN regressor demonstrated the strongest goodness-of-fit line with an R^2 score of .92. However, the Mean Absolute Error and MAPE are slightly higher for the KNN weighted model overall, while the OLS regression model performed worse with respect to MSE and RMSE, meaning OLS had more high error values. In this case, I would choose KNN in this case, but were the dataset to be larger in terms of observations or features, OLS may take precedence, as it runs faster and can be more highly tuned to specifications.
